place.name: THURNE
place.gazetteerText: THIRNE or Thurne, a parish in Flegg district, Norfolk; 4 miles N by E of Acle, and 7½ NE of Brundall r. station. Post town, Burgh, under Norwich. Acres, 660. Real property, £1,534. Pop., 210. Houses, 49. The living is a rectory, annexed to Ashby. The church is Norman. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
